## Demo Script (Step-by-Step)

### Setup
1. Connect both laptops to the **same WiFi network** as the RPI
2. Note down all IPs: RPI = `X`, Laptop A = `Y`, Laptop B = `Z`

### Demo Flow

| Step | Laptop A (Defender) | Laptop B (Attacker) | What Audience Sees |
|------|--------------------|--------------------|-------------------|
| 1 | Start [laptop_gcs.py](file:///d:/AniEngg/Subjects/Sem6/IDP/Main/laptop/laptop_gcs.py), connect to RPI | вҖ” | Normal dashboard, green status |
| 2 | Drone flying, telemetry streaming | Run `scanner.py` вҖ” discovers RPI on port 5760 | Attacker's terminal shows drone found |
| 3 | Normal monitoring | Run `sniffer.py` вҖ” starts capturing telemetry | Attacker sees live GPS, battery, mode |
| 4 | Dashboard suddenly shows wrong GPS | Run `telemetry_spoofer.py` вҖ” sends fake coords | Dashboard map jumps to fake location |
| 5 | Dashboard shows "Battery: 3%!" panic | Spoofing battery to critical level | Operator might trigger emergency landing |
| 6 | **Drone actually lands or changes mode** | Run `cmd_injector.py` вҖ” sends `{"command":"land"}` | The drone physically responds to attacker's command |
| 7 | Dashboard shows anomaly alerts | вҖ” | Anomaly detection fires: `MODE_CHANGE`, `GPS_SPOOFING` |

